main event: A witness in South Dartmouth, Massachusetts observed an unusual aerial phenomenon on April 6, 1967.
interesting points: The witness observed a bright, disc-shaped object in the sky that was emitting a bright white light from the center.
The object appeared to be metallic in nature and was silent in operation.
The witness attempted to photograph the object but was unable to do so due to the speed at which it disappeared from view.
The report was forwarded to Project Blue Book for further investigation.
The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes.
sighted object: a disc-shaped object with a bright white light
photographs: yes, but the witness was unable to capture the object
